Meiosis adalah proses perkembiakan sel yang mengakibatkan produksi sel-sel germas (sel kelamin) yang memiliki jumlah kromosom setengah dari sel induknya (kromosom haploid). Meiosis terjadi pada sel kelamin (sel spermatozoa dan sel ovum) dan pada organ reproduksi (testis dan ovarium).

In this paper we study the effects of online review information asymmetry between buyers and peers in online markets through an empirical analysis using panel dataset from an online e- commerce platform in Japan during 2009 through 2020. Using a simultaneous system GEE model that simultaneously models online review asymmetries between buyers and sellers and buyers, we empirically examine the effects of peers' online review information on online buyers' purchases from online markets using panel dataset during 24 months from 2010 through 24 through 26 June 2040. The results show that online review information has significant positive effects not only online buyers but also online peers regarding online purchases from online e-commerce markets. The findings suggest that online review plays an important role for online buyers' online purchases from e- commerce markets through information asymmetries that exist between buyers and online peers during online purchases from an online market.
